  "prompt": "My girlfriend for 4years cheated 3 times. I found out 2 month ago. She started talking to a guy as a friend. He called her babe, what should I do?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're experiencing this. Dealing with infidelity and the uncertainty it brings can be incredibly painful and confusing. Here are a few steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Communicate Openly**: Have an honest conversation with your girlfriend about your feelings and concerns. Express how her actions have affected you and seek clarity on her intentions.\n\n2. **Set Boundaries**: If certain behaviors, like her talking to someone who calls her \"babe,\" make you uncomfortable, it's important to discuss and establish boundaries that respect both of your needs.\n\n3. **Reflect on the Relationship**: Take some time to consider whether this relationship is meeting your emotional needs and if trust can be rebuilt. Think about what you want and deserve in a partnership.\n\n4. **Seek Support**: Talking to a trusted friend, family member, or a professional counselor can provide you with guidance and help you process your emotions during this difficult time.\n\n5. **Prioritize Self-Care**: Make sure to take care of your own well-being. Engage in activities that you enjoy and that help reduce stress.\n\nRemember, you deserve a relationship built on trust, respect, and mutual support. Whatever decision you make, ensure it's one that aligns with your happiness and emotional health.",
